# --- .env (copy to .env, fill in, never commit) ---
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR-ANON-KEY


# =====================================================================
# WIRING — preview → hosted app (3 steps)
# =====================================================================
#
# 1. Backend: run 001_gpu_matchmaking_core.sql in the Supabase SQL editor.
#    (schema + matches/coverage views + RLS + audit + seed data)
#
# 2. Frontend: scaffold a Vite React app, drop in the files:
#       npm create vite@latest gpu-matchmaker -- --template react
#       cd gpu-matchmaker
#       npm install @supabase/supabase-js lucide-react
#       # place: src/App.jsx (GPUMatchmaker.jsx), src/lib/supabase.js, src/lib/api.js
#       # Tailwind: https://tailwindcss.com/docs/guides/vite  (the app uses core utilities)
#       # Fonts: npm i geist @fontsource/mona-sans  (or keep the Google Fonts @import in the file)
#
#    Then flip the data layer in App.jsx — replace the local `dataLayer` object with:
#       import { loadData, updateRequirement } from "./lib/api";
#       const dataLayer = { loadData, updateRequirement };
#    Nothing else changes; the useEffect loader and saveEdit handler already call it.
#
# 3. Host: deploy the static build to Vercel or Cloudflare Pages (free tier is fine).
#       - add VITE_SUPABASE_URL / VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY as env vars in the host
#       - turn on Supabase Auth (email magic-link or Google SSO)
#       - the `authenticated` RLS policy = logged-in team members get full read/write
#
# The anon key is safe in the browser *because* RLS is on — it grants nothing
# until a user authenticates. Never ship the service_role key to the frontend.
#
# Concurrency note: the optimistic guard compares updated_at (a timestamptz).
# If two saves ever collide on the same microsecond, swap to an integer `version`
# column bumped by the trigger and guard on that instead — same pattern.
